      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOBY KEEPING (1) has been in the placings at his last two runs, most recently when second (30.89) in a Special conditions race over 530m at this track. Can make amends this time. DURAN PANTERA (3) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (31.09) at Gawler behind Handover in a Grade 6. Has the pace to be prominent. Can feature again. BLACK EYED GIRL (4) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fourth (20.20) in a TG1-4W at this track. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to her name from four starts. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. COMPTON ROCKS (2) is a last-start placegetter worth considering.",
